## Project Overview

Prabodhika is a Next.js study platform for Indian college students — featuring a content hub (PDFs, notes, links), community Q&A with threaded discussions, and a personal dashboard. Authentication supports credentials (email/password), Google, and GitHub.

## Tech Stack

- **Framework**: Next.js 16.2.4 (App Router)
- **Language**: TypeScript 5 with `@/*` path alias (maps to project root)
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS v4 with `@tailwindcss/postcss`
- **Auth**: NextAuth.js v4 (credentials + OAuth), JWT strategy
- **Database**: MySQL via `mysql2/promise` connection pool
- **Email**: External PHP service at `https://mail.protoolvault.in/send-verification.php` (called from API routes with `MAIL_API_KEY` header)
- **Fonts**: Google Fonts (Yeseva One for display, Outfit for body) loaded via `next/font/google`

## Commands

```bash
npm run dev      # Start dev server on http://localhost:3000
npm run build    # Production build
npm run start    # Start production server
npm run lint     # Run ESLint
```

No test framework is configured.

## Architecture

### Route Groups (App Router)

- `app/(public)/` — Public pages: `page.tsx` (homepage with Hero, Features, How It Works, CTA sections), `about/page.tsx`
- `app/(auth)/` — Auth pages: login, register, verify-email, forgot-password, reset-password (each with a `*Client.tsx` component)
- `app/(protected)/` — Protected routes: `home/` (dashboard with HomeClient), `upload/` (content upload)
- `app/complete-profile/` — Profile completion wizard (university → college → course + year) with `CompleteProfileClient.tsx`
- `app/api/` — API routes (see below)

### Route Protection Flow

The protected layout (`app/(protected)/layout.tsx`) enforces a 3-step gate server-side:

1. **No session** → redirect to `/login`
2. **Email not verified** → redirect to `/verify-email`
3. **Profile not completed** → redirect to `/complete-profile`

### Key Files

- `types/next-auth.d.ts` — Extends NextAuth `Session.user` type with `id`, `email_verified`, `profile_completed`
- `lib/auth.ts` — NextAuth config: providers (Credentials, Google, GitHub), JWT/session callbacks, `signIn` callback for OAuth auto-create
- `lib/db.ts` — MySQL connection pool (`mysql2/promise`), exported as `db`
- `lib/requireProfile.ts` — Client-side hook for profile completion enforcement
- `app/providers.tsx` — Wraps app in `SessionProvider`
- `app/theme-provider.tsx` — Dark/light theme via Tailwind `dark` class + localStorage
- `app/layout.tsx` — Root layout: loads fonts, wraps in Providers + ThemeProvider
- `app/globals.css` — Design tokens, component styles (`.btn-primary`, `.hero-section`, etc.), animations, responsive breakpoints

### Shared Components

- `components/Navbar.tsx` — Authenticated user nav (used in protected layout)
- `components/NavbarPublic.tsx` — Public nav with mobile hamburger menu
- `components/Footer.tsx`, `components/FooterPublic.tsx` — Footer variants
- `components/HeroIllustration.tsx` — SVG illustration for homepage hero
- `components/SearchSelect.tsx` — Reusable async search/create dropdown. Props: `api` (search endpoint), `createApi` (create endpoint), `extraData` (additional payload), `onSelect` callback, `placeholder`

### Authentication Flow

**Credentials**: Email/password → bcrypt hash comparison → JWT issued
**OAuth (Google/GitHub)**: OAuth flow → `signIn` callback auto-creates user with `email_verified=true` → JWT issued
**Session callback** (`lib/auth.ts`): On every session access, fresh user data is fetched from DB to sync `email_verified`, `profile_completed`, and academic profile fields (`university_id`, `college_id`, `course_id`)

### Database Schema (key tables)

**users**: `id, name, email, password, provider, provider_id, verification_code, email_verified (bool), university_id, college_id, course_id, year, profile_completed (bool)`

**universities**, **colleges**, **courses**, **subjects** — Academic reference data (id, name, plus foreign keys where applicable)

**contents** — User-uploaded content (referenced by API routes `api/content/*`)

### API Routes

| Route | Method | Purpose |
|-------|--------|---------|
| `api/auth/[...nextauth]` | GET/POST | NextAuth handler |
| `api/auth/register` | POST | Register user, generate verification code, call email service |
| `api/auth/verify-email` | POST | Verify code, set `email_verified=true` |
| `api/auth/forgot-password` | POST | Trigger password reset email |
| `api/auth/reset-password` | POST | Update password with bcrypt hash |
| `api/auth/resend-verification` | POST | Resend verification code |
| `api/universities` | GET | List universities |
| `api/colleges` | GET | List colleges (filtered by `university_id`) |
| `api/courses` | GET | List courses (filtered by `college_id`) |
| `api/subjects` | GET | List subjects (filtered by `course_id`) |
| `api/user/complete-profile` | POST | Update user's academic profile |
| `api/content/create` | POST | Create new content entry |
| `api/content/check-duplicate` | POST | Check for duplicate content |
| `api/upload-file` | POST | Handle file uploads |
| `api/test-db` | GET | Database connectivity test |

